decks.notes: The key concept of this deck is to control the game by using counter spells, removal, and card advantage to disrupt the opponent's strategy and protect your own game plan. Ertai Resurrected serves as the commander, providing a powerful control ability to counter spells and sacrifice creatures for more control options. The deck includes a variety of counter spells such as Cryptic Command, Counterspell, and Force of Will, as well as removal spells like Damnation and Toxic Deluge to clear the board. Card advantage is gained through cards like Baleful Strix, Jace, the Mind Sculptor, and Mystic Confluence, while searches and card selection are supported by cards like Demonic Tutor and Preordain. The deck also features a win condition with Wurmcoil Engine and Torrential Gearhulk.

The key concept of this deck is to utilize the versatility of Niv-Mizzet Reborn as a control commander. The deck includes a diverse range of spells and creatures across all colors to ensure maximum value from Niv-Mizzet Reborn's ability to dig deep into the deck and potentially draw multiple cards. The deck contains various interaction spells like Fatal Push, Vindicate, and Swords to Plowshares, along with powerful creatures like Baleful Strix and Voice of Resurgence to control the board. The mana base is carefully constructed to support the five-color requirements of the commander, allowing for flexibility in casting spells of any color. Overall, the goal is to out-value opponents and control the game until victory is secured.

This deck revolves around the commander, Karlov of the Ghost Council, an aggressive creature that gains counters whenever you gain life. The main focus is to generate life gain through various sources such as lifelink creatures, spells like Blessed Alliance and Authority of the Consuls, and the commander's ability itself. By gaining life, Karlov becomes a massive threat that can quickly take over the game. The deck also includes disruption elements like Drannith Magistrate and Opposition Agent to disrupt opponents' strategies. It features a combination of removal spells like Vindicate and Anguished Unmaking, as well as board wipes such as Toxic Deluge. The mana base is built to support the deck's black and white color identity, with a mix of dual lands and fetch lands for consistency.
